#### Grouped analysis with a retail calendar

Groups work exactly as they do with the standard calendar. Each group gets a complete fiscal calendar.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
contoso::sales |>  #<1>
  dplyr::group_by(store_key) |>  #<2>
  qtd(
    .date = order_date,  #<3>
    .value = margin, #<4>
    calendar_type = "445", #<5>
    fiscal_year_start = 2 #<6>
  ) |>
  calculate() |> #<7>
  dplyr::collect() #<8>
```
:::



1. Pass data through
2. Optionally select a grouping key
3. Select the date column to index
4. Select the value calumn to aggregate
5. Select the type of non-standard calendars
6. Select the non-standard calendar fiscal start date -- Sunday closest to February 1st
7. Return a lazy_tbl
8. Return a tibble

